<title>USA: Rational Software acquisition deal cleared.</title>
<headline>Rational Software acquisition deal cleared.</headline>
<dateline>SANTA CLARA, Calif. 1997-07-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Rational Software Corp said its proposed $839 million acquisition of Pure Atria Corp has received antitrust clearance by the Department of Justice.</p>
<p>The companies will hold special stockholders' meetings on July 30 to vote on the deal, it said.</p>
<p>Rational and Atria write development tools, a type of software that helps programmers write other software.</p>
